external_knowledge:
- The 'bust' measurement refers to the fullest part of the chest;
- The 'waist' measurement refers to the narrowest part of the torso, typically around the navel;
- 'Average measurements' are calculated by summing the measurements for each customer and dividing by the number of records.

- "more than one order" implies a count greater than 1;
- "total number of orders" is the count of unique order IDs;
- "average order amount" is the mean of the total amounts of the orders.

- "Most popular sizes" are determined by the number of distinct orders for each size of a clothing item;
- The query ranks sizes within each clothing item and selects the top-ranked size;
- The brand and category information is also included for each item.

- "Unisex" clothing items are designed to fit both male and female customers;
- "Cotton" is a common material used in clothing for its comfort and breathability;
- "Total spent" refers to the cumulative amount a customer has spent on orders;
- "Shoulder measurement" and "bust measurement" are specific body measurements used to ensure a good fit for the clothing item.

- 'Smallest size' refers to the smallest available size for each clothing item;
- 'Latest records' refer to the most recent entries in the customer measurements, clothing items, sizes, and inventory;
- 'In stock' means the inventory quantity is greater than 5;
- 'More expensive than $20' means the price of the clothing item is greater than 20.

- "chest size" refers to the bust measurement of clothing items;
- "crown jewel" is a metaphor for the brand with the highest average bust measurement;
- "kingdom of fashion brands" refers to the collection of all brands in the dataset.

- "jewels of the wardrobe" refers to the most popular or top-selling clothing items;
- "shine the brightest" refers to the items that generate the highest revenue;
- "their respective categories" refers to the different categories of clothing items.

- "blossomed into orders" refers to items that were ordered;
- "planted in the inventory" refers to items being added to the inventory;
- "within a year" refers to a period of less than 365 days;
- "the duration of their journey from inventory to order" refers to the number of days between `date_added` and `order_date`.

- "Crown jewel" refers to the most valuable or prominent item in a collection or business;
- "Shining the brightest" metaphorically means generating the highest total revenue;
- "Total revenue" is the sum of the total amounts of all orders for an item;
- "Total items sold" is calculated as the total revenue divided by the average price of the item.

- "shining star" is a metaphor for the brand with the highest average revenue;
- "stands out" implies being the best or most prominent;
- "across all its items" indicates that the revenue is calculated for all items associated with the brand.

- 'Brand A' refers to a specific brand of clothing;
- 'Reorder level' is the inventory level at which a new order should be placed to replenish stock;
- 'Shipped' indicates that the order has been dispatched to the customer;
- The total amount is formatted by replacing periods with commas and then removing all commas.

- "garments" refers to clothing items;
- "royal makers" refers to brand names;
- "stands taller than half the realm's average" refers to an average price greater than half the average price of all clothing items;
- "average price" is calculated as the mean price of all items in the same category and brand.
